# Outils MCP HDW – Résumé d’utilisation

Voir les descriptions détaillées dans [README_hdw-mcp-server.md](mdc:README_hdw-mcp-server.md).

- search_linkedin_users: Recherche utilisateurs (filtres: keywords, first_name, last_name, title, company_keywords, location, industry, education, count, timeout)
- get_linkedin_profile: Profil détaillé (user, with_experience, with_education, with_skills)
- get_linkedin_email_user: Lookup par email (email, count, timeout)
- get_linkedin_user_posts: Posts utilisateur (urn, count, timeout)
- get_linkedin_user_reactions: Réactions utilisateur (urn, count, timeout)
- get_linkedin_chat_messages: Messages (user, company?, count, timeout)
- send_linkedin_chat_message: Envoyer message (user, text, company?)
- send_linkedin_connection: Invitation (user)
- send_linkedin_post_comment: Commenter (text, urn activité/comment)
- get_linkedin_user_connections: Connexions (connected_after?, count?)
- get_linkedin_post_reposts: Reposts (urn activity, count)
- get_linkedin_post_comments: Commentaires (urn activity, sort, count)
- get_linkedin_post_reactions: Réactions (urn activity, count)
- get_linkedin_google_company: Recherche sociétés via Google (keywords[], with_urn?, count_per_keyword)
- get_linkedin_company: Société (company alias/url/urn)
- get_linkedin_company_employees: Employés (companies[], keywords?, first_name?, last_name?, count)
- linkedin_sn_search_users: Sales Navigator (nombreux filtres, count)
- get_linkedin_conversations: Conversations (connected_after?, count?)
- google_search: Recherche Google (query, count)

Notes: Certains endpoints nécessitent `HDW_ACCOUNT_ID` (gestion). Les URN attendent des préfixes (`fsd_profile:`, `activity:`).